{
  "texts": [
    "The three main types of Swin Transformers are Base, Large, and Tiny, and the two specific scales used in this study are Base and Large.",
    "The attention mechanism serves as a computational model designed to identify and assign weights to relevant elements within a sequence or set.",
    "This process involves computing an attention weight by learning the relationship between a query (Q), a key (K), and a value (V).",
    "Subsequently, this weight is applied to the corresponding value to produce a weighted representation.",
    "In practical applications, the Self-Attention mechanism has found extensive use."
  ]
}